#Text=FC Barcelona defeats Sevilla FC 5-4 to win UEFA Super Cup 2015
#Text=Saturday , August 15 , 2015
#Text=On Wednesday , Catalonia -based football club FC Barcelona defeated Seville -based football club Sevilla 5 – 4 to win the 2015 UEFA Super Cup .
#Text=The match was held in Boris Paichadze Dinamo Arena in the city of Tbilisi , Georgia .
#Text=Pedro , who may leave for Manchester United , scored the winning goal of the match in the 115th minute .
#Text=This was the fifth UEFA Super cup won by Barcelona .
#Text=Barcelona had stronger possession of the ball in front of Sevilla .
#Text=The match saw nine yellow cards , four for Barcelona players and five for Sevilla players .
#Text=A total of 41 fouls were committed in the match .
#Text=A total of nine goals were scored in the match , with the first goal scored in the opening minutes of the game .
#Text=Barcelona defender Mascherano committed a foul in the 2nd minute and thus Sevilla got a free kick .
#Text=Banega converted the free kick into goal in the 3rd minute of the game .
#Text=Minutes later , Sevilla 's Krychowiak committed a foul and this early lead was soon equalised as Barcelona forward Lionel Messi scored a similar style free kick .
#Text=Krychowiak received a yellow card in the 14th minute and Barca were awarded another free kick for Banega 's foul on Rakitić .
#Text=Leo Messi converted this free kick into a goal , giving the lead to Barcelona after 16 minutes of game play .
#Text=This was Messi 's 36th goal in 37 games in 2015 .
#Text=Minutes before half time , Luis Suárez assisted Rafinha and the Brazilian tripled the lead for the Catalans .
#Text=First half ended with scoreline 3 – 1 with only one booking .
#Text=Within ten minutes of the second half , Suárez scored the fourth goal in the 52nd making it a one-sided match .
#Text=Five minutes later , Reyes scored a close ranged shot making the score 4 – 2 .
#Text=In the 63rd minute , Andrés Iniesta was substituted off for Sergi Roberto .
#Text=Iniesta made his 550th appearance for Barcelona .
#Text=After this substitution , the goal difference kept on dropping .
#Text=In the 71st minute , Mathieu was booked for a foul on Vitolo .
#Text=Referee awarded a penalty kick for Sevilla .
#Text=Gameiro perfectly converted it into a goal making it 4 – 3 .
#Text=Within the next ten minutes , Sevilla equalised with Barcelona .
#Text=Konoplyanka scored an easy tap-in to bring Sevilla from 4 – 1 to 4 – 4 .
#Text=Within half an hour , the one-sided match changed into a tensed match .
#Text=Coke in the 87th minute and Banega in the 90+2 minute were booked for committing foul on Suárez .
#Text=The game ended in 4 – 4 .
#Text=And thus it was extended to additional time .
#Text=Additional time saw five more yellow cards .
#Text=Pedro was substituted in for Mascherano in the 93rd minute and in the next minute , he received a yellow card for foul on Vitolo .
#Text=Barcelona won a free kick in the dying minutes of the game .
#Text=Messi 's kick became an indirect assist to Pedro who netted it in the top corner .
#Text=It was the winning goal of the game .
#Text=This was Pedro 's 99th goal in the Catalonia jersey .
#Text=By this victory , Barcelona joined A.C. Milan as the most successful club .
#Text=Both the teams have earned the title five times .
#Text=This trophy was Messi 's and Iniesta 's 25th trophy with Barcelona .
#Text=Messi was awarded Man of the match .
#Text=After the match , he said , " We are delighted to start the season with this win , but it was tough [ ... ]
